 this center, primarily through the highly-publicized  “ 5-5555 ” extension in addition to heavily-utilized administrative extensions. Public Safety units include UIC Police Officers, Security personnel, and Student Patrol staff. On average, 75,000 calls for service are generated annually in the Communications Center. The Police Communications Center also monitors the campus video surveillance system that consists of 900+ cameras, the Lenel entry/exit alarm system, the Keltron Fire alarm system, and the Startel Emergency Kiosks and panic buttons which can be found all around campus grounds.          About    Back to main content           Mission, Vision, and Core Values    Command Staff    Division of Support Services and Internal Affairs     Internal Affairs    Training, Equipment, Accreditation and Records    Technical Services Unit      Patrol Operations Division     Honor Guard    Crisis Intervention Training (CIT)    Field Training Program    Grant Writing Committee    Range Officers    Evidence Technicians    Bicycle Patrol    Tactics and Scenario Unit      Special Operations Division     Investigations Unit    P.A.C.E.    Crime Statistics    Student Patrol      Hospital/Clinic Security Division     Security Sergeants    Security Officers    Security Guards      Telecommunication Center    News & Alerts     Join Our Team    Campus Safety Tools    Maxwell Street Station History    Filming at UICPD                     UIC Logo         University  Police           Locations    Springfield    Urbana-Champaign    Regional Campuses      Related Links    Office of the Vice Chancellor of Administrative Services    Office of Preparedness and Response    Housing    Office of Access and Equity    Campus Advocacy Network    Dean of Students    Transportation Services    Parking         Contact   943 West Maxwell Street, MC 268, Chicago, IL 60608-1563  Phone: Emergency:  (312) 355-5555 | General: (312) 996-2830  uicpd@uic.edu        Social Media Accounts             UIC.e